Step 8: Manually Create Configuration Files
If the npx tailwindcss init -p command still doesnâ€™t work, you can manually create the configuration files:

Create tailwind.config.js:

javascript
Copy
// tailwind.config.js
export default {
  content: [
    "./index.html",
    "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
};
Create postcss.config.js:

javascript
Copy
// postcss.config.js
export default {
  plugins: {
    tailwindcss: {},
    autoprefixer: {},
  },
};